{
 "name": "RPlog_Miracles_and_Mayhem",
 "title": "Miracles and Mayhem",
 "summary": "Searching for her injured friend Paul Nighman, the anxious young busker Shenner arrives at the seaside home of Paul's old colleague, the aged Mon Calamari professor Dr. Molari Canto. Canto gently but pointedly interrogates her about who she is and what Paul means to her before relenting and directing her to the cliffside where Paul sits brooding over the sea. There Shenner and the recovering Paul share a tender, halting reconciliation, talking through his guilt over hurting Jessalyn, his plans to leave, and the deepening, uncertain bond between them. The day unfolds into a quiet picnic and a tearful, wordless comfort, and Paul carries the exhausted girl to rest before confiding his troubled feelings to Molari.",
